   Stelco Pipe-Making Plant
</HL>
<DATE>
05/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   STE.A CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   HAMILTON, Ontario -- Stelco Inc. said it plans to build a
pipe-making plant in Welland, Ontario, at a cost of 60
million Canadian dollars ($50.6 million).
   The steel maker said construction will begin immediately,
for completion in early 1992. The plant will have annual
capacity of 140,000 metric tons, the company said.
</LP>
