bonds are priced at par to yield from 6.10% in 1991 to 7.05%
in 2000, changed from 6.10% in 1991 to 7.10% in 2000. Capital
appreciation bonds are priced to yield to maturity from 7.25%
in 2001 to 7.65% in 2011 and 2012, changed from 7.25% in 2001
to 7.60% in 2010-2012. Series 1990 A refunding bonds consist
of current interest serial bonds priced at par to yield from
6.10% in 1991 to 7.35% in 2006 and 2007, changed from 6.10%%
in 1991 to 7.35% in 2005. The bonds are rated double-A by
Moody's and single-A-plus by S&amp;P, excluding capital
appreciation bonds, which are AMBAC-insured and rated
triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P.
                                                                                                       


                                                                                                       

