   ADWEEK: The top three executives of A/S/M Communications,
owner of Adweek, couldn't be reached regarding speculation
that they were in discussions to sell part or all of the
company to Affiliated Publications, Boston. Affiliated
already owns the Boston Globe, as well as Billboard and other
trade publications. Staffers at Adweek have been told that
troubled A/S/M, which has already folded a number of its
publications, is seeking a cash infusion from an outside
investor. Affiliated executives couldn't be reached.
                                                                                                       

   JOINT VENTURE: Chiat/Day/Mojo, Los Angeles, said it set up
a joint venture with Han Brindfors Advertising, Stockholm.
The two agencies plan to develop a pan-European network of
agencies. Chait/Day said the joint venture would be owned
equally, with agencies planned for Italy, France and Spain.
                                                                                                       

   DELLA FEMINA: Jerry Della Femina, chairman of Della
Femina, McNamee WCRS, denied speculation the agency is
selling its Boston office. Industry executives say Della
Femina has been in discussions to sell the Boston office to
Arnold Advertising, a Boston shop headed up by former Della
Femina executive Ed Eskandarian. Arnold Advertising
executives couldn't be reached.
                                                                                                       

