<HL>
   International Brief -- KLM Royal Dutch Airlines:
   Fiscal 1990 Initial Results
   Show 9% Drop in Earnings
</HL>
<DATE>
05/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   KLM
</CO>
<LP>
   KLM Royal Dutch Airlines reported that rising aviation
fuel prices were partly responsible for a 9% drop in net
income in its year ended March 31.
   Although the results are only preliminary, the Dutch
airline said earnings fell to 340 million guilders ($181
million) from 374 million guilders in fiscal 1989. The
company will issue final figures June 13.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   KLM also said its earnings were hurt by higher levels of
depreciation and an increase in financial expenses.
   Despite the drop in net, the Dutch airline reported a
revenue gain of 8.3% to 6.5 billion guilders from 6 billion
guilders.
   Operating profit before interest payments fell to 310
million guilders from 390 million guilders in fiscal 1989.
</TEXT>
