<HL>
   Business Brief -- Richton International Corp.:
   Jewelry Firm Says It Had
   Loss for Fiscal 4th Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   RHT
</CO>
<LP>
   Richton International Corp., a jewelry concern, said it
expects to report a loss for its fiscal fourth quarter and a
profit for the year.
   For the year-earlier quarter, ended April 30, Richton
posted a loss of $3.2 million, or $1.16 a share, including a
$2.9 million one-time charge related to the downsizing of its
New York office. Net sales were $5.4 million. For fiscal
1989, it posted a loss of almost $3 million, or $1.07 a
share, on net sales of $30.5 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first three quarters of fiscal 1990, Richton
posted a profit of $528,000, or 19 cents a share, on net
sales of $18.2 million. The company said in New York that it
experienced a "significant weakening" in the period just
ended, but continues to take steps to reduce costs and
improve sales.
</TEXT>
